This extension is a new version of "Interpreter events tracker for Bilingual" legacy extension, and will replace it in the future.

Extension detects certain events triggered by interpreters in client's platform (such as login, logout or start taking calls) as part of his/her regular use of such platform. This events information allows Bilingual to collect statistics about interpreters performance and effective working time.

No personal information (either interpreter's nor client's) is collected, stored or distributed in any way, and no information is extracted from other websites nor web apps that could be used by Bilingual interpreters. Only client-specific platform used by Bilingual LS interpreters in his/her daily work are analyzed for events tracking.

Client ID: 4 (client-uls)
